[Screenshot 5: Printer Job (wait/notify)]
The printer waits when the tray is low on pages and automatically resumes 
once the refill thread adds more pages and notifies the waiting thread.

[Screenshot 6: Deadlock Demonstration]
Shows a deadlock scenario where Thread 1, 2, and 3 are all waiting for 
locks held by each other, causing the program to hang indefinitely.

[Screenshot 7: Deadlock Solved]
Shows the resolution of the deadlock. By enforcing a consistent global 
lock ordering, all threads are able to acquire their required locks 
and finish execution successfully.
